\begin_layout Section
Calibration Instructions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

DummyLoad stores a calibration table and other configuration settings in
 the EEPROM of the on-board PIC microcontroller.
 The table consists of up to 60 rows mapping uncalibrated meter readings
 to corrected power values.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

DummyLoad linearly interpolates between the provided calibration points.
 Program the EEPROM using an Arduino board (Uno, Nano, etc) and the provided
 configuration sketch by following the steps below.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Download the 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Arduino IDE"
target "https://www.arduino.cc/en/software"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and install it on a computer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Download the 
\family typewriter
uDummyLoadConfig
\family default
 configuration sketch and open it within the Arduino IDE.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Follow the instructions in the configuration sketch to configure the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

DummyLoad to operate in 
\series bold
\shape italic
calibration mode
\series default
\shape default
 (to bypass any previously-loaded calibration table) and with 
\series bold
\shape italic
extended 0.001W precision
\series default
\shape default
 (to increase the calibration accuracy.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Perform the calibration measurements by applying known power levels and
 recording the meter readings.
 One way to do this is to insert a calibrated wattmeter in series with the
 feedline; another method is to measure the peak input voltage with a high-imped
ance oscilloscope and compute the input power as 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{in}=v_{pk}^{2}/100$
\end_inset

; yet another is to use a rig with a power output reading you trust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Create a table mapping meter readings in milliwatts (first column) to the
 known power readings in milliwatts (second column.) 
\series bold
\shape italic
\color red
Sort the table in ascending order by the column of meter readings.
 All values should be whole numbers of milliwatts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Follow the instructions in the Arduino sketch to disable calibration mode,
 set precision back to 0.1W, and load the calibration table.
\end_layout

