\begin_layout Paragraph*
Voltage-Divider Resistance Error
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The division factor of the peak detector voltage-divider is 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{div}=1+R_{top}/R_{bot}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $R_{top}=100k\Omega$
\end_inset

 (nominal) is the value of the upper resistor and 
\begin_inset Formula $R_{bot}=10k\Omega$
\end_inset

 (nominal) is the value of the lower resistor.
 The error in the voltage division factor 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{div}$
\end_inset

 due to deviation of the resistance values from nominal, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta R_{top}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta R_{bot}$
\end_inset

, is given by the total differential approximation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Delta A_{div}\approx\frac{1}{R_{bot}}\Delta R_{top}-\frac{R_{top}}{R_{bot}^{2}}\Delta R_{bot}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The maximum error occurs when 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta R_{top}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta R_{bot}$
\end_inset

 have different signs (i.e.
 when the upper resistance is higher than nominal and the lower resistance
 is lower than nominal, or vise versa) and is given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max|\Delta A_{div}|\approx\frac{1}{R_{bot}}|\Delta R_{top}|+\frac{R_{top}}{R_{bot}^{2}}|\Delta R_{bot}|
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Writing the resistance errors in terms of the resistor percent tolerance
 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $|\Delta R_{top}|=(t/100)R_{top}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $|\Delta R_{bot}|=(t/100)R_{bot}$
\end_inset

 results in the formula
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max|\Delta A_{div}|\approx\frac{2t}{100}\frac{R_{top}}{R_{bot}}=\frac{2t}{100}(A_{div}-1)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
With a nominal division factor of 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{div}=11$
\end_inset

V/V and resistor tolerance of 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0.1\%$
\end_inset

, the maximum error in the division factor is 0.02V/V.
 The corresponding maximum error in the power reading is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Delta P_{err}\approx2P_{in}\frac{\max|\Delta A_{div}|}{A_{div}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The error is 0.004W for 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{in}=1.0$
\end_inset

W and 0.073W for 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{in}=20.0$
\end_inset

W.
\end_layout

